The Biden-Harris Administration is taking new actions to promote responsible innovation in artificial intelligence (AI) and protect people's rights and safety. They are emphasizing the importance of driving responsible, trustworthy, and ethical innovation with safeguards to mitigate risks and potential harms. Today, Vice President Harris and senior officials will meet with CEOs of leading AI companies to underscore this responsibility. The Administration has previously released a Blueprint for an AI Bill of Rights, an AI Risk Management Framework, and a roadmap for a National AI Research Resource. They have also taken actions to address bias and discrimination in AI, as well as national security concerns in areas like cybersecurity and biosecurity.